<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2014/12/02/springone2gx-2014-replay-building-reactive-applications-with-reactor-and-the-reactive-streams-standa4d">SpringOne2GX 2014 Replay: Building Reactive applications with Reactor and the Reactive Streams standa4d</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon news-and-events"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/news">News and Events</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/c910c2f6520a5977a836d74e86e07cb4?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Pieter Humphrey</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2014-12-02 10:21:00.0">December 2, 2014</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1870" href="/blog/2014/12/02/springone2gx-2014-replay-building-reactive-applications-with-reactor-and-the-reactive-streams-standa4d#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Recorded at SpringOne2GX 2014. </p>
<p>Speakers: Jon Brisbin, Stephane Maldini </p>
<p>Slides:<a href="http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/spring-one2gx-2014reactivestreams-41130280">http://www.slideshare.net/SpringCentral/spring-one2gx-2014reactivestreams-41130280</a> </p>
<p> This session will introduce attendees to the Reactive Streams project, a new initiative between reactive software's heavy-hitters like Pivotal, Typesafe, Netflix, Twitter, and others. Since Pivotal's own Reactor framework implements this informal standard, we'll demonstrate how to build applications that can connect to other Reactive Streams implementations in a completely non-blocking way.</p>
</div>
</section>
