<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2014/11/26/spring-roo-1-3-1-rc1-available-with-important-bug-fixes">Spring Roo 1.3.1 RC1 available with important bug fixes</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/c910c2f6520a5977a836d74e86e07cb4?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Pieter Humphrey</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2014-11-26 10:21:00.0">November 26, 2014</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1863" href="/blog/2014/11/26/spring-roo-1-3-1-rc1-available-with-important-bug-fixes#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Spring Roo 1.3.1 RC1 Release Candidate is available.</p>
<p>Spring Roo jar files have been published to Maven Central. As always, the release is available in the Spring IO repository. </p>
<p>The candidate release fixes serious issues: </p>
<ul>
<li> running reverse engineering. </li>
<li> installing third-party addons. </li>
</ul>
<p>It is highly recommended that all Spring Roo users upgrade to this version. </p>
<p>For full details on the changes made in the release, please refer to the <a href="https://jira.spring.io/secure/ReleaseNote.jspa?projectId=10340&amp;version=14836">Release Note in Jira</a>.</p>
<p>For more project specific information please see the <a href="https://projects.spring.io/spring-roo/">Project Page</a> and <a href="https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-roo">GitHub</a></p>
</div>
</section>
